claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: A table summarizing influenza vaccines by trade name and manufacturer, presentations, age indications, micrograms of hemagglutinin (HA) per dose (µg HA per 0.5 mL or specified volume), route of administration, and mercury content. It includes categories for standard-dose egg-based IIV4 (15 µg/strain), cell culture-based cIIV4 (15 µg/strain), high-dose IIV4 (60 µg/strain), adjuvanted IIV4 (15 µg/strain), recombinant HA vaccine RIV4 (Flublok, 45 µg/strain), and live attenuated LAIV4 (virus count). Evidence: Flublok Quadrivalent (RIV4) shows 45 µg/0.5 mL; standard-dose egg-based IIV4 vaccines show 15 µg/0.5 mL per strain. The table directly shows Flublok contains 45 µg HA per dose versus 15 µg per dose in standard-dose influenza vaccines, which supports the claim.
